Corps Members have been advised to embrace discipline, hard work and selfless service during and after their service year. The Director-General of the National Youth Service Corps, Brigadier General Muhammad Kaku Fadah stated this on Sunday while addressing Corps Members during his visit to Zamfara and Katsina States orientation camp in preparation for the forthcoming 2022 Batch ‘B’ Orientation Course. He said as leaders should avoid getting-rich-quick syndrome to have a better future. -Advertisement- Fatah advised the Corps Members not to embark on any unauthorized journey and also avoid night journeys. He urged them to be security-conscious and take care of their safety. “Don’t travel at night and obtain permission from NYSC if you must travel”, the DG said. While in Katsina, the Director-General also paid a courtesy visit to the Commander, 17 Brigade of the Nigerian Army, Brigadier General IA Ajose. General Fadah thanked the Brigade for its support for NYSC Katsina State, especially accommodation, welfare for Corps Members serving at the brigade and sponsorship of activities during orientation exercises. He solicited more support for the Scheme in future engagements, especially on Corps security. POLL The Brigade Commander in his response congratulated General Fadah on his appointment as the DG NYSC, while he promised more support from the Brigade for NYSC Katsina State.